# Local Port Isolation

When working in this repository, always keep each project on a separate localhost port.

- Never reuse the same local HTTP/HTTPS port across different projects.
- Treat port overlap as a blocking issue and fix launch profiles before further work.
- Prefer explicit project-targeted run commands:
  - `dotnet run --project /Users/rodneyamoschery/dev/RodneyPortfolio/RodneyPortfolio.csproj --launch-profile http`
  - `dotnet run --project /Users/rodneyamoschery/dev/RodneyPortfolio/ChurchWebsite/ChurchWebsite.csproj --launch-profile http`
- Keep local routes local only; do not redirect localhost traffic to production domains.

## Required checks before testing

- Confirm each project's `Properties/launchSettings.json` uses non-overlapping `applicationUrl` values.
- Confirm the expected app identity on each port (e.g., portfolio routes on `5076`, church routes like `/Prayer` on `7075`).

